items.postText: Nayeem: "Liton has made up his previous dropped catch by 2 stumpings, it's BD's match to lose from here now."

items.text: flighted full outside off, and he drills a drive straight to Soumya Sarkar at cover. Well stopped

items.text: tossed up on off, and he shovels a drive to deep extra cover. Mehidy finishes with 2 for 28

items.text: full outside leg stump, and the straight drive takes an inside-edge onto his pads, and then rolls away to short third man for one
items.shortText: Mahmudullah to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 leg bye

items.text: arm ball outside off stump. It's a half-tracker, but the batsman can't put it away. The punch goes straight to Mashrafe
items.shortText: Mahmudullah to Hasan Ali, no run

items.text: good length on off, and spinning into the batsman. He backs away to cut, but the ball is inside-edged onto his body

items.text: length ball on middle stump. The ball goes down the leg side
items.shortText: Mahmudullah to Hasan Ali, 1 wide

items.text: big appeal for lbw but not given. It's a slider that angles in after landing on off. Hits his front leg, but would've clearly missed leg stump
items.shortText: Mahmudullah to Hasan Ali, no run

items.text: full on off, and spinning sharply inwards now. Pushed to mid off
items.shortText: Mahmudullah to Hasan Ali, 1 run

items.text: good length on leg stump, and cramping the batsman for space. Whipped away to square leg. Mahmudullah finishes with 1 for 38
items.shortText: Mahmudullah to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

items.text: good length on middle stump, but angling into his pads. Misses the flick, and the delivery hits his front leg. Muted appeal for lbw, but the ball was always angling down leg
items.postText: Param-Toronto: "BD has this strange habit of celebrating too early... Hope they don't repeat that and play with the same intensity till 49.6 overs"
items.shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

items.preText: Venkat: "Ahh, if Afghan had won their match against Ban, then they would have been in finals as Bangla is winning this match. Unfortunate for them, IND deserve final spot for their consistency and Afg for their temperament"
items.text: full outside off stump. Angling further away, but Hasan frees his arms, and slaps this over cover! Bounces just inside the boundary
items.shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Hasan Ali, FOUR runs

items.text: length ball angling away once again. Tries to cut this square, but bottom-edges it to point instead
items.shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Hasan Ali, no run

items.text: full on middle stump, and Hasan has no option but to tap it towards point. Wants the single, but Mehidy has pounced onto this stray ball in a flash
items.shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Hasan Ali, no run

items.text: back of a length on off, and he swings hard towards the leg side. But he's toe-ended this shot, and the skyer is comfortably taken at mid on running to his left
items.postText:
Abhay S Rajput: "I think this tournament is the closest fought Asia cup as of now. Kudos to all the participating teams specially the sensational and ever-improving Afghanistan team."

Akshat: "No matter what happens today or any game before the World Cup, I think Pakistan are one of the best teams in English conditions. So they still will be favourites in the World Cup"
items.shortText: Mustafizur Rahman to Hasan Ali, OUT

dismissal.text: Hasan Ali c Mashrafe Mortaza b Mustafizur Rahman 8 (11b 1x4 0x6) SR: 72.72

items.text: good length outside off, and punched off the back foot to deep point. Enough time to run back for the second, but they choose not to

items.text: good length outside off, and angling away from the left-hander. Tries to muscle a cut away, but mistimes to point
items.shortText: Rubel Hossain to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

items.text: short outside leg stump, and soaring over the batsman's head. Left alone
items.postText: Badri: "Bangladesh too has been good in this tournament. They too have lost out on important players like Tamim and Shakib today but have found ways to win games. At the end of the day, winning matters and B'desh won important games to get into finals. Afg are not ready for the finals yet as they seem to lose the plot in the 50th over."
items.shortText: Rubel Hossain to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 wide

items.text: full outside off, and the slower ball goes through to Liton on the bounce. The batsman can't get bat to it
items.shortText: Rubel Hossain to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

items.text: back of a length on middle, and the extra bounce deceives the batsman. Tries to pull square, but the bat's nowhere near the ball
items.shortText: Rubel Hossain to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

items.text: full on middle and leg, and that's been drilled to the left of long on for a single. Wild throw from the deep, but there's no extra run conceded
items.shortText: Rubel Hossain to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

items.text: full outside leg stump, and he works this to wide long on once again. Just a single though. NRR touching 11 now
